A1. Sounds of sarcasm ~ HARS
A5. Half a Washington city, county, or river ~ WALLA
A10. Land of the lost? ~ LALA
A14. 1966 NL batting champ ~ ALOU
A15. Mix with ~ ADDIN
A16. Beame and others ~ ABES
A17. Senator whose surname should be stressed on the second syllable ~ JONCORZINE
A19. Edith Hamilton specialty ~ MYTH
A20. Dreyfus Affair words ~ JACCUSE
A21. Diplomatic mission ~ EMBASSY
A23. "And ___ lot" (Alice in Chains lyric) ~ IDOITA
A24. Their blades go through water ~ OARS
A25. Former congressman whose surname really ends with a "K" sound ~ NEWTGINGRICH
A31. Modern musical offering ~ NEWCD
A34. Memorizing methods ~ ROTES
A35. Nazi's beginning ~ NEO
A36. Hit ___ court (get lucky in tennis) ~ ALET
A37. Group seconds ~ BETAS
A38. The prez ~ CINC
A39. A solo shot is one ~ RBI
A40. Old Nick ~ DEVIL
A41. Emotion that drives vengeance ~ WRATH
A42. Another senator whose surname is stressed on the second syllable ~ DANIELINOUYE
A45. Musical numbers for one ~ SOLI
A46. Talking head ~ NEWSIE
A50. Heard (of) ~ GOTWIND
A53. Lapped, so to speak ~ SITTING
A54. English word from the Latin for "courtyard" ~ AREA
A55. Big pol whose surname really rhymes with "tortellini" ~ DICKCHENEY
A57. First word of an infamous memoir ~ MEIN
A58. "... who lived in ___" ~ ASHOE
A59. The nation's most powerful lobby, according to "Fortune" ~ AARP
A60. Tech support wait time, typically ~ EONS
A61. Babushka ~ SCARF
A62. Charlie Brown often wears one ~ MITT

